* {{a|UK}} {{IPA|/ˈæ.dɪ.tɪv/|lang=en}}
* {{a|US}} {{IPA|/ˈæ.də.tɪv/|[ˈæ.ɾə.tɪv]|[ˈæ.ɾə.ɾɪv]|lang=en}}

===Adjective===
{{en-adj}}

# {{lb|en|mathematics}} Pertaining to [[addition]]; that can be, or has been, [[added]].
# {{lb|en|mathematics|of a [[function]], etc.}} That is [[distributive#English|distributive]] over [[addition]].
#: {{ux|en|Matrix multiplication is '''additive''', in that <math>M\vec v+M\vec w=M(\vec v+\vec w)</math>.}}
# {{lb|en|group theory|of a group, semigroup, etc.}} Whose [[operator]] is identified as [[addition]].
#: {{ux|en|It is natural to look at a finite cyclic group as an '''additive''' group.}}
# {{lb|en|chemistry}} Pertaining to chemical [[addition]].
# {{lb|en|genetics}} Of or pertaining to [[gene]]s (or the interaction etc. of such genes) which govern the same trait and whose effects work together on the [[phenotype]].

